@q384566678 an unprivileged user cannot mount other kind of file systems.
In Linux 4.18 it will be possible to mount a FUSE file system in an user namespace, so we can take advantage of it and emulate overlay in user space: https://github.com/containers/fuse-overlayfs.

There is already support for it plugged into containers/storage and it is enabled with `--storage-opt  overlay.mount_program=/usr/bin/fuse-overlayfs`.  If you'd like you can already play with it on Rawhide where Linux 4.18 is available

@giuseppe Thanks for your explanation.
Now there is a [development plan](https://github.com/projectatomic/buildah/blame/master/developmentplan.md#L7) in the community that is related to this. I thought that the type of driver could be improved to complete this plan, but it doesn't seem to be.
I also want to advance this work, but I have no direction at present. Could you give me some advice? Thank you very much!
